         <OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1">
            <TITLE>
               <P>New Homes Construction — Offsite</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>NH2</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="45211000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="WORKS"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>LHC is carrying out early engagement for renewal of its-site housing framework (NH1) Framework Agreement in respect of the construction of residential dwellings incorporating offsite systems for the public sector. The Framework is aimed at delivering housing, apartments, care homes and multi-occupancy dwellings. The form of the framework will be subject to a pre-tender engagement process, commencing with this PIN and is proposing to hold pretender market engagement for prospective tenders. Contract sizes will cover small infill sites and larger schemes.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">1000000000.00</VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="44211100"/>
                  <CPV_SUPPLEMENTARY_CODE CODE="DA03"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UK"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>Various Offsite hosuing projects across the UK.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>LHC is re-procuring its NH Framework for offsite housing for the public sector. The primary aim of the Framework is to deliver housing, apartments, multi-occupancy buildings including care homes, sheltered accommodation and student accommodation.</P>
                  <P>The Framework will be open for use by all public sector organizations including local authorities and registered providers. A list of eligible organizations is available at www.lhc.gov.uk/24</P>
                  <P>The Framework is currently split into 3 workstreams:</P>
                  <P>— Workstream 1 Volumetric Systems,</P>
                  <P>— Workstream 2 Panelized Systems,</P>
                  <P>— Workstream 3 Construction using offsite systems.</P>
                  <P>Each workstream was offered across various geographical regions across the UK. It is proposed that the revised framework will also be split into regional lots to encourage SME's to apply.</P>
                  <P>The previous framework had lots covering the following areas: Southwest England, Southeast England, London, Midlands, Northern England, Wales and Scotland.</P>
                  <P>The Framework was also divided by project size, and whether the project was a low or high rise project.</P>
                  <P>The format of the lots for the new framework will be decided after pretender engagement.</P>
                  <P>It is proposed the new framework will cover the following areas:</P>
                  <P>1. main contractor services for delivering offsite systems;</P>
                  <P>2. manufacturers who only want to offer supply and installation of offsite systems;</P>
                  <P>3. consortiums or groups who can deliver main contractor service for off-site systems;</P>
                  <P>4, delivery of modular houses;</P>
                  <P>5. delivery of apartments and multi-occupancy buildings;</P>
                  <P>6. delivery of rooftop units;</P>
                  <P>7. delivery of a range of size of projects from small infill sites to larger projects.</P>
                  <P>Companies interested in this opportunity should register via https://procontract.due-north.com</P>
                  <P>LHC proposes to hold a pretender engagement workshop and details will be provided through the e-tendering portal.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>2018-05-16</DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <CONTRACT_COVERED_GPA/>
         </PROCEDURE>
         <COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
            <INFO_ADD>
               <P>Suitable for all economic operators including Small and Medium Enterprises (SMEs), any selection of tenderers will be based solely on the criteria set out for the procurement, and the framework will be concluded on the basis of the Most Economically Advantageous Tender.</P>
               <P>Available to use on all publicly funded projects, see our website for existing and potential users:</P>
               <P>https://www.lhc.gov.uk/24</P>
               <P>Please register your interest at:</P>
               <P>https://www.lhc.gov.uk/join-as-a-supplier</P>
               <P>Then click on “Register and Login”.</P>
            </INFO_ADD>
